choices.text:
too much fish in the rivers, lakes and sea waters, as much as 40+ pounds a day, the rivers and lakes where I used to drown in the local Brook Trout and Mulberry (small indigenous trout like Brook Trout) , are now practically dead,never seen water running free , since the communist era, and just a decade after communism ended the fish are starving, grown without access to other ground foods simply bred in a tanks and fed with Alfalfa grown in artificial cooling-stored bodies of water, where there is little to no wild flora for the fish to feed on.The fish grow weak and small, because of their lack of physical activity after being kept in place by the communist dictatorship, the buildings that are supposed to transport the fish, are in poor condition and a good portion of the water from commotion and even punched holes in the tanks where fish are transported,when the people working this job get fed up with no pay or lack thereof .

My advice I would give to Romania a young country are :

1. Do import and export on a limited scale, nothing too big.

2. Pay the troops and workers before you pay yourself, upgrade their homes, their salary and benefit packages, human welfare before house welfare.

3. Make use of a mobile government, one that doesn't stay in one place, and works off of a roving schedule to each county or given area.

4. Abolish the Christian Church, If you make God be blind and God be mute
